The US&nbsp;Preventive Services Task Force (USPSTF) recently published recommendations on risk assessment, genetic counseling, and genetic testing for BRCA mutations and BRCA-related cancers. This JAMA Patient Page explain the new recommendations.&nbsp;<br />
<br />
Jin J.&nbsp;Should I Be Tested for BRCA Mutations?&nbsp;JAMA. 2019;322(7):702.&nbsp;
